						<summary>

						<p>This records a similar gift of 100 sheep for a perpetual lamp in the same temple by <hi rend="bold">Nakkaṉ Aṟiñjigai</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Pirāntaka-Pallavaraiyaṉ</hi>, a chief evidently called after <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> (Vide No. 70 above). The assembly of the village <hi rend="italic">(peruṅguṟi-perumakkaḷ)</hi> agreed to maintain this gift.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
